amarokfs (0.4.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Version 0.4.2 from kde-apps.de by Jan Zarnikov <jan.zarnikov@gmail.com>
  * patched to use common ubuntu-paths (/usr/ instead of /usr/local/)
  * Added and modfied patch that allows to disable the OSD while running
    amarokFS (original posted to the comments at kde-apps.de by Matthias
    Fehring) and to disable the hint shown at startup.
  * Patch to the cover-extractor - now the correct cover is chosen independent
    from the size of the cover-preview
  * Fixed behavior on dual-screen setup: The setting button won't show up any
    more when mouse is on second screen.
  * uses modified isimplydark-theme as standard
  * Added amarok-script so that we are able to access amarokFS from
    within amarok. So the desktopmenu entry can also get removed.
  * Added xml-tag for theme-file which allows to supress stupid dcop-results.
    Instead a defaultText can be defined.

 -- Martin Kossler <martin.kossler@students.uni-marburg.de>  Wed, 14 Feb 2007 19:15:31 +0100
